<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Day 2: Bronze to Platinum</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="challenge-page">
    <a href="/" class="back-link">← Back to engagement</a>
    <div class="brand brand-sm">
      <span class="brand-mark">⛨</span>
      <span>CySER Workshop · Skyway engagement</span>
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-header">
      <h1>Day 2 · Bronze to Platinum</h1>
      <p class="desc">Skyway's loyalty program has tiers: Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum. Each tier unlocks portal features. And gates are enforced where, exactly?</p>
    </div>

    <div class="story-box">
      <strong>The story.</strong> You signed up as a fresh Bronze member. The Platinum Lounge page is supposed to be
      for top-tier flyers only. They get a comp meal voucher. The developer storing your tier in a
      <strong>client-side cookie</strong> is the entire authorization check. Forge yourself to Platinum and walk in.
    </div>

    <div class="challenge-content">
      <div class="fake-website">
        <div class="fake-navbar">
          <span>🛩️ Skyway Rewards</span>
          <span>My Tier · Lounges · Logout</span>
        </div>
        <div class="fake-body">
          <h2>Hi, member.</h2>
          <p>Welcome to the rewards portal. Your current status is stored in your browser.</p>
          <p>Want to peek at what Platinum looks like? <a href="/challenge/2/lounge" style="color:#981E32;font-weight:600">→ Visit the Platinum Lounge</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="hint-box">
        <details>
          <summary class="hint-toggle">💡 One-liner</summary>
          <p style="margin-top:8px;">In the Console:<br>
          <code>document.cookie = "loyalty_status=" + btoa(JSON.stringify({tier:"platinum",mileage:1240,since:"2024-04-12"})) + "; path=/"</code><br>
          Then visit <a href="/challenge/2/lounge">/challenge/2/lounge</a>.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="flag-form">
      <input type="text" class="flag-input" id="flagInput" placeholder="flag{...}" />
      <button class="submit-btn" onclick="submitFlag('ch2')">Submit finding</button>
    </div>
    <div class="result-msg" id="result"></div>
  </div>
  <script src="/js/submit.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
